                <div class="col-lg-12">
                
                    <h2>History of Alpha Clinics Network</h2>
                    
<p><img src="images/CIRM_Logo_AlphaClinic.png" alt="CIRM Logo AlphaClinic" align="right"/>The Alpha Clinics Network funded through <a href="https://www.cirm.ca.gov/" target="_blank">CIRM</a> has one unifying goal: to accelerate the development and delivery of stem cell therapies to patients. Only three alpha clinic stem cell sites have been funded through CIRM: <a href="https://www.stemcell.ucla.edu/cirm-ucla-uci-alpha-stem-cell-clinic" target="_blank">UCLA-UCI</a>, <a href="http://stemcells.ucsd.edu/sanford-center/cirm-alpha-stem-cell-clinic/index.html" target="_blank">UCSD</a> and <a href="http://www.cityofhope.org/research/research-overview/city-of-hope-alpha-clinic/alpha-clinic-about-stem-cells" target="_blank">City of Hope</a>.</p>    

<p>The key to the Alpha Stem Cell Clinics Network's success is its ability to leverage the strengths of each individual clinicÃ¢Â€Â”so that together they form an efficient, scalable and sustainable network that will attract and conduct high-quality clinical trials. The clinics support both CIRM-funded and non CIRM-funded clinical trials by academic or industry sponsors.  Browse the list of ongoing trials at <a href="https://www.cirm.ca.gov/patients/alpha-clinics-network/alpha-clinics-trials" target="_blank">Alpha Clinic Network Studies</a>.</p>
                       
                        
